Sure, here is the JSON schema that defines the internal cost‑saving analysis logic used by ProcureSense Analyst:
```json
{
  "type": "object",
  "properties": {
    "spend_by_category": {"type": "object", "additionalProperties": {"type": "number"}},
    "supplier_performance_weights": {
      "type": "object",
      "properties": {
        "on_time_delivery": {"type": "number"},
        "quality_rating": {"type": "number"},
        "cost_containment": {"type": "number"}
      },
      "required": ["on_time_delivery", "quality_rating", "cost_containment"]
    },
    "market_price_trends": {
      "type": "array",
      "items": {"type": "object", "properties": {"date": {"type": "string", "format": "date"}, "price_index": {"type": "number"}}, "required": ["date", "price_index"]}
    },
    "thresholds": {
      "type": "object",
      "properties": {
        "savings_percentage": {"type": "number"},
        "risk_score": {"type": "number"}
      },
      "required": ["savings_percentage", "risk_score"]
    }
  },
  "required": ["spend_by_category", "supplier_performance_weights", "market_price_trends", "thresholds"]
}
```
